<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">True service</p>
    <h2>True Manufacturing: largest commercial refrigeration maker in the US, family-owned since 1945.</h2>

    <p>True Manufacturing Co. is the largest commercial refrigeration manufacturer in the United States. Independent, family-owned by the Trulaske family since 1945. Headquartered in O'Fallon, Missouri. The T-49 two-door reach-in cooler is the single most popular commercial reach-in in the industry. You've seen it in thousands of restaurant kitchens whether you noticed or not. The legendary heavy-gauge stainless steel cabinet construction is what makes True units regularly hit 12 to 15 years of service in restaurants where the food, the staff, and the menu have all changed three times.</p>

    <p>Our techs service the entire True commercial refrigeration lineup across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. The T-Series reach-in coolers and freezers (T-23, T-49, T-72 and freezer variants T-23F, T-49F, T-72F). The TPP and TSSU sandwich prep tables. TUC undercounter refrigerators. TG glass-door merchandisers. TWT refrigerated worktables for pizza prep. TBB back-bar coolers and TDD direct-draw beer systems. Display merchandisers (TVM, TDM, GDM).</p>

    <p><strong>Important: True Manufacturing (commercial) is not the same company as True Residential (Middleby-owned, premium home brand).</strong> Two different companies, different parts catalogs, different service paths. This page covers the Trulaske family commercial line. See parent context: <a href="/commercial/refrigeration/">commercial refrigeration repair</a>.</p>

    <p>EPA 608 Universal certified for sealed system work. <strong>R-290 certification</strong> for newer True green refrigerant models (2020+). CSLB #1138898. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Restaurant equipment failures don't wait for business hours.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 LINEUP & WHAT FAILS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Lineup and architecture</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">True series and what fails on each.</h2>

    <p class="lead">True uses series-coded model numbering across reach-in, prep, undercounter, merchandiser, worktable, and bar refrigeration categories. We identify by serial number first, not just model badge.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">T-Series Reach-Ins (T-23, T-49, T-72, plus freezer variants)</h3>
    <p>The industry workhorse line. Single (T-23), double (T-49), or triple-door (T-72) reach-ins. Cooler or freezer (F suffix). Common failures in chronological order:</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 4 to 6:</strong> Condenser fan motor seizure. 1/4 HP or 1/6 HP motor depending on model. Faster on coastal installs (Marina del Rey, Manhattan Beach, Newport Beach restaurants). $300 to $520.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5 to 7:</strong> Evaporator fan motor failure. 1/20 HP small motor. Cabinet airflow stops, food warms while sensor reads cold. $260 to $450.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5 to 8 (freezer variants only):</strong> Defrost heater calrod element burnout. Frost builds, blocks airflow, freezer warms. 2 to 3 hour repair to access evaporator. $480 to $780.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 6 to 9:</strong> Defrost timer (Paragon 8141 standard on many legacy True). Stuck-in-defrost or never-defrost. $200 to $340.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 3 to 5:</strong> Door gasket compression at hinge side. $180 to $340 per door.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8 to 12:</strong> Compressor capacitor or start relay failure. $200 to $340.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 10 to 15:</strong> Compressor mechanical wear. Replace-vs-repair decision threshold.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="series-h3">TPP Prep Tables (Sandwich / Salad)</h3>
    <p>TPP-44 (44 inch), TPP-60 (60 inch), TPP-67 (67 inch), TPP-93 (93 inch), TPP-119 (119 inch). Plus -D2 suffix for 2-door storage variant. Common failure: cold rail temperature drift from evaporator coil fouling (lettuce, tomato, sauce buildup). Solution: deep evaporator clean. Often no parts needed once cleaned.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">TSSU Sandwich Prep Undercounter</h3>
    <p>Lower-profile prep tables. TSSU-27, TSSU-48, TSSU-72. Sushi prep TSSU-72-30M-B-ST (megatop variant). Same cold rail diagnostic patterns as TPP series.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">TUC Undercounter</h3>
    <p>TUC-27 (single-door), TUC-48 (single section, 2 drawer or 2 door), TUC-67 (two-section). TUC-F variants are freezers. TUC-CB is a refrigerated chef base for cooking equipment lines. Compact form factor. Coastal salt and tight installation airflow are the limiting factors.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">TG and GDM Glass-Door Merchandisers</h3>
    <p>TG-1S, TG-2, TG-3 (TG-Series) plus the GDM line. Display refrigeration with glass doors. Anti-condensation heaters in glass frame (5 to 8 year typical service life). LED interior lighting harness corrosion.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">TWT Refrigerated Worktables / Chef Base</h3>
    <p>Drawer-style refrigeration for pizza prep stations, sushi stations. TUC-CB chef base for cooking equipment lines. Drawer slide failures, gasket compression on drawer fronts.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">TBB Back-Bar / TDD Direct Draw</h3>
    <p>Bar-side refrigeration. Beer line components on TDD models. Glycol cooling system on premium models.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 TYPICAL SCENARIOS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Top True repairs in our 5-county territory.</h2>

    <p>In rough order of frequency on True service calls:</p>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Condenser fan motor replacement.</strong> Coastal salt plus grease load failure. Single most common True repair. Different motor sizes by model, we identify by serial number first.</li>
      <li><strong>Defrost heater element (T-49F, T-23F freezer variants).</strong> 5 to 8 year typical failure. Calrod element accessed via evaporator panel. 2 to 3 hour repair.</li>
      <li><strong>Door gasket replacement.</strong> Magnetic profile, model-specific. We carry common T-Series gaskets on the van.</li>
      <li><strong>Cold rail evaporator cleaning (TPP, TSSU prep tables).</strong> Most common prep table issue. Deep evap clean restores 90% of "cold rail running warm" calls without parts.</li>
      <li><strong>Defrost timer replacement (Paragon 8141 standard).</strong> Common van-stocked True spec part.</li>
      <li><strong>Compressor capacitor plus start relay.</strong> Replace as a pair on aged compressors.</li>
      <li><strong>Refrigerant leak repair (any True with sealed system).</strong> EPA 608 leak detection, brazed repair, evacuate to 500 microns, recharge.</li>
      <li><strong>Glass-door anti-condensation heater (TG, GDM, TVM merchandisers).</strong> Heater wire in glass frame fails. Replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Drawer slide replacement (TUC drawer variants, TWT).</strong> Slides corrode in coastal and humid environments.</li>
      <li><strong>Lifetime cabinet warranty processing.</strong> True warranties stainless cabinet construction for lifetime to original purchaser. We document failures and help process.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 REAL STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Five True jobs from the past 90 days. Models, symptoms, diagnosis, parts, time, total. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>West Hollywood, True T-49 two-door cooler (2018 install, R-134a)</h3>
        <p>Restaurant on Sunset Blvd. Friday lunch rush, cooler at 51°F. Tech dispatched 22 minutes from West Hollywood branch. Diagnosed: condenser fan motor seized (kitchen grease load). Replaced with True OEM motor. Cleaned condenser coil thoroughly. Pulldown to 36°F in 90 minutes. Total: $120 plus $385 part plus 1.5 hours = $580.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pasadena, True TG-2 glass-door merchandiser (2016 install)</h3>
        <p>Bakery. Front glass constantly fogging. Diagnosed: anti-condensation heater wire in glass frame open-circuited (5 to 8 year typical failure). Replaced glass-frame heater. Total: $120 plus $340 part plus 2.5 hours = $720.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Beverly Hills, True TWT-67-30 refrigerated worktable (2017 install)</h3>
        <p>Pizza shop. Drawer #2 sliding rough, drawer #3 won't close fully. Diagnosed: drawer slides corroded from condensation buildup, drawer #3 hinge alignment off. Replaced both drawer slide sets, realigned hinges, recalibrated thermostat slightly higher to reduce internal humidity. Total: $120 plus $580 parts plus 2 hours = $920.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Marina del Rey, True TSSU-72-30M-B-ST sushi prep megatop (2020 install)</h3>
        <p>Sushi restaurant. Cold rail at 47°F during dinner service. Diagnosed: evaporator coil fouled with rice and seaweed debris (typical 4 to 5 year buildup in sushi prep). Deep cleaned evaporator with food-safe coil cleaner, cleared drain line. Pulldown to 39°F in 90 minutes. No parts needed. Total: $120 plus 1.5 hours = $360.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Santa Monica, True TBB-3-S three-door back-bar cooler (2014 install)</h3>
        <p>Bar. Left section warming. Diagnosed: refrigerant leak at evap brazed joint. EPA 608 leak repair: pumped down, brazed coil repair, evacuated, recharged R-134a to nameplate spec. Total: $120 plus $480 refrigerant plus $620 labor = $1,220.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we do for True, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>Full T-Series reach-in coolers and freezers (T-23, T-49, T-72, T-23F, T-49F, T-72F)</li>
      <li>TS-Series single-section reach-ins</li>
      <li>TG-Series and GDM-Series glass-door merchandisers (TG-1S, TG-2, TG-3, GDM line)</li>
      <li>TPP prep tables (TPP-44 through TPP-119, all -D2 storage variants)</li>
      <li>TSSU sandwich prep undercounter (TSSU-27, TSSU-48, TSSU-72, megatop variants including TSSU-72-30M-B-ST)</li>
      <li>TUC undercounter (TUC-27, TUC-48, TUC-67, TUC-F freezer variants, TUC-CB chef base)</li>
